Theſe mooſells are ſometimes made of leather, and ſtampt full of holes, or elſe cloſe, but they are unſavoury and unwholſome; for if it be Allomd leather, the Allome is offenſive: if it be liquored leather, the greaſe and Tanners 
                     •
                  uze are full as unpleaſant, beſides they are too cloſe, and too hot, and both make an horſe ſick, cauſe him to forbeare reſt, and retaine his dung longer in his bodie then otherwiſe he would do;
